
---


@startuml

' Define classes with attributes and associations

class Resident {
    - name: String
    - streetAddress: String
    - phoneNumber: String
    - emailAddress: String (optional)
    + schedulePickup(): void
}

class PickupRequest {
    - description: String
    - pickupTime: Time (8:00-14:00)
    - requestedDate: Date
    - status: Status
    + submitRequest(): void
}

class VolunteerDriver {
    - name: String
    - vehicleId: String
    - availableDays: List<Day>
    + registerAvailability(): void
}

class Vehicle {
    - id: String
    - maxStorageCapacity: Double
    - currentLoad: Double
    + assignPickupRoute(): void
}

class PickupRoute {
    - date: Date
    - startTime: Time
    - endTime: Time
    - pickups: List<PickupRequest>
    + calculateOptimalRoute(): void
}

class DistributionCenter {
    - location: String
    - employee: Employee
    + receiveItems(): void
    + tagWithRFID(): void
}

class FoodBank {
    - location: String
    + receiveNonPerishableFood(): void
}

class Item {
    - description: String
    - category: Category
    - quality: Quality
    - RFIDTag: String (optional)
    + correctDescription(): void
}

class Category {
    - id: Integer
    - name: String (e.g., "Baby Clothing", "Microwave")
}

class Employee {
    - name: String
    - role: Role
    + examineQuality(): void
    + assignCategory(): void
    + notifyClients(): void
    + arrangeDelivery(): void
}

class Client {
    - name: String
    - address: String
    - preferredCategories: List<Category>
    + requestNotification(): void
    + requestDelivery(): void
}

class DeliveryService {
    - driver: VolunteerDriver
    - item: Item
    - client: Client
    + deliverItem(): void
}

class Day {
    - name: String (e.g., Monday, Tuesday)
}

enum Status {
    Scheduled, Completed, Cancelled
}

enum Quality {
    Good, Fair, Poor
}

enum Role {
    PickerUp, Distributor, Coordinator
}

' Associations

Resident --> PickupRequest : places
PickupRequest --> PickupRoute : assigned to
PickupRoute --> Vehicle : assigned to
Vehicle --> VolunteerDriver : driven by
VolunteerDriver --> PickupRoute : drives
PickupRequest --> Item : contains
DistributionCenter --> Item : receives
FoodBank --> Item : receives non-perishables
Employee --> DistributionCenter : works at
Employee --> Client : notifies
Client --> DeliveryService : requests
DeliveryService --> VolunteerDriver : uses
DeliveryService --> Item : delivers
Item --> Category : categorized as
Employee --> Item : examines and tags

@enduml

---

### 🧩 Explanation of Key Components:

- **Resident**: Submits a pickup request.
- **PickupRequest**: Represents items to be picked up, with time and date constraints.
- **VolunteerDriver & Vehicle**: Drivers manage vehicles used for pickup routes.
- **PickupRoute**: A daily route plan based on volunteer availability and item logistics.
- **DistributionCenter & FoodBank**: Items are sorted and distributed here.
- **Item & Category**: Items are tagged and categorized after inspection.
- **Client & DeliveryService**: For clients who need delivery assistance; delivery is arranged via volunteers.

